#Children are curiosity machines, and will learn for themselves, if you give them the resources and freedom ! This is the power of #onlinelearning ! And even better, it's #free ! Why waste money on overpriced #EduTech apps which lock students into their platform ?

When we force #students to learn what we think is important for them to know, this backfires, because we end up making them allergic to #learning! This is why self-directed #onlinelearning is so much more effective than the #EduTech apps like #Byju's and #Toppr !
We are all #selflearners. Good teachers just help to catalyze the process! This is true for #onlinelearning and #elearning as well

##Learning is hard work and it's easy to lose your #motivation . #Fitness #challenges are done as groups, because buddies help you through rough patches when your intrinsic motivation flags. They offer support. Can we apply the same principle to #onlinelearning ? #elearning ?

We #play #games and #sports as #teams, which is why we enjoy them so much. How can we create that same sense of #community and #camaraderie in #onlinelearning for #students who want to #learn something new?

The Edutech startups (#Byju , #Toppr and #Vedantu ) have raised tons of money. They have a huge opportunity to use #onlinelearning to empower #students.Sadly, they use #elearning to create harm by dumbing students down, and make them dependent on being spoon fed
